According to the text, the following calculations are required for a bias audit of an Automated Employment Decision Tool (AEDT):
1. Calculate the number of applicants assessed by the AEDT in each category required to be reported to the U.S. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission (EEOC) pursuant to the EEO Component 1 report;
2. Calculate the number of applicants selected by the AEDT in each category required to be reported to the EEOC pursuant to the EEO Component 1 report;
3. Calculate the selection rate for each category required to be reported to the EEOC pursuant to the EEO Component 1 report;
4. Ensure that the calculations separately calculate the impact of the AEDT on sex categories, race/ethnicity categories, and intersectional categories of sex, ethnicity, and race;
5. Indicate the number of individuals the AEDT assessed that are not included in the required calculations because they fall within an unknown category.
